The paper presents a framework for motion planning among a group of robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a maneuver automaton and control policy suggests a focus on system control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of feedback strategies and modular design also suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
